<subSubSection id="83B4655DA87BFFA3FD4FF958FDA70B15" lastPageId="100" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="99" pageNumber="99" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CB1136D6A87BFFA3FD4FF958FDA70B15" blockId="99.[701,1228,1530,1759]" lastBlockId="100.[93,620,212,527]" lastPageId="100" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="99" pageNumber="99">
COMMENTS: In the original description, Hartert had the single specimen, sexed by the collector as a male, but noted by Hartert as perhaps not fully adult. Subsequently, additional material was received, including an adult male (Rothschild and Hartert: 1900: 44â€“45), showing that the originally described specimen was missexed. Only the single specimen was present when the original description was published. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="AF3F4B27A87CFFA3FD81FE51FF6108AC" author="Hartert, E." pageId="100" pageNumber="100" pagination="369 - 371" refId="ref95589" refString="Hartert, E. 1901. On some birds from north-west Ecuador. Novitates Zoologicae 8: 369 - 371, pl. V." type="journal article" year="1901">Hartert (1901: 371</bibRefCitation>
, pl. V) gave a description of the adult male, noted that the immature male was like the female but larger, and provided a plate picturing both male and female.
</paragraph>
